<title>USA: Alpha sees Q3 charge for planned sales.</title>
<headline>Alpha sees Q3 charge for planned sales.</headline>
<dateline>WOBURN, Mass. 1996-11-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Alpha Industries Inc said on Monday it would take a charge not exceeding $2.6 million, or $0.26 per share, in the third quarter for its planned divestiture of its European ceramics manufacturing operation and digital radio subsystem product line.</p>
<p>The company said the planned sales were part of its strategic focus on components for the wireless industry. It said it expected to achieve profitability in the fourth quarter because of increasing order activity in the wireless area.</p>
